Governor Samuel Ortom has confirmed that the decomposed body of Emmanuel Ajama, an official of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has been found. Ajama went missing while on duty in Gwer West Local Government  Area of the state. The Nation gathered that he was kidnapped by bandits. Ortom was speaking when the state commandant of the Corps, Sule Okeji, and his delegation visited the Government House, Makurdi. Ortom said he had prayed fervently for Ajama’s safe. The governor called for more deployment of NSCDC officials in the state, adding that the police were inadequate.